The paper presents a model selection approach that focuses on reducing computational resources required to identify state-of-the-art performance from large collections of candidate models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on sentiment analysis, which is a common task in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of bandit theory, which is a common approach in Reinforcement Learning (cs.LG) and Multi-Armed Bandits (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of train-test splits, which is a common approach in Computer Vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SI, ordered from most to least likely.
